This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and neural networks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to NLP and neural networks. Additionally, since the paper discusses the performance of different models, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields often involve comparing the performance of different neural network architectures.
